1) Right click on Start menu -> run -> type cmd ->  type GPUPDATE /FORCE  
When it finishes restart the computer.  This usually fixes the issue.
 
2) remapping the share drive usually fixes the issue.
(right click on start -> open file explorer -> double click on 'This PC' -> Click on Computer -> map network drive - > Folder: -> Finish
 
3) Right click on start menu -> run -> type services.msc and press enter
    when you are in the services window
    scroll down until you see Workstation.
    Make sure the status is 'running' and startup type should be 'Automatic'
    Even if it's already running,  you can right click and restart the service and it will fix the issue.
